
1. Screen Scraping Methods
 Common Initial Steps

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Click on Blank Process
Step 3: Go to the Design tab (Top Ribbon)
Step 4: Click on Screen Scraping
Step 5: Use mouse to select the application/window
Step 6: Screen Scraper Wizard will open

 a) Full Text Method

Step 1: In the Scraper Wizard, locate Scraping Method dropdown
Step 2: Select Full Text (default option)
Step 3: Click Finish



 b) Native Method

Step 1: In the Scraper Wizard, select Native from dropdown
Step 2: Choose option:

Check No Formatting → for raw text
Uncheck → to keep text position

Step 3: Click Finish

 c) OCR Method

Step 1: In the Scraper Wizard, select OCR
Step 2: Choose OCR Engine:

Tesseract OCR
UiPath Screen OCR

Step 3: Click Finish


 2. Data Scraping & Variable Display
Data Scraping (Web Page)

Step 1: Open a web page (e.g., Google/Amazon results)
Step 2: Go to UiPath Studio → Click:

Table Extraction (Modern) OR
Data Scraping (Classic)

Step 3: Click on first data element (e.g., product name)
Step 4: Click on second similar element

Step 5: Wizard auto-detects pattern

Step 6: Rename column (e.g., "Product Name")
Step 7: Click Next

Step 8: Click Extract Correlated Data
Step 9: Select another field (e.g., Price)

Step 10: Click Finish


Creates Extract Structured Data activity
Stores data in variable: ExtractDataTable
 Display Data in Message Box

Step 1: Drag Output Data Table activity
Step 2: Set:

Input: ExtractDataTable
Output: Create variable dtString

Step 3: Drag Message Box activity
Step 4: Enter:

dtString

Step 5: Run the workflow
